# Data Flow Diagram — Student Result Management System

## Level 0 (Context Diagram)

Shows the entire system as a single process interacting with external entities.

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    Staff([🧑‍🏫 Staff])
    Student([🎓 Student])
    System["Student Result\nManagement System"]
    DB[(SQLite Database)]

    Staff -- "Register / Login\nCredentials" --> System
    Staff -- "Student Info\n(Name, Roll No, Year)" --> System
    Staff -- "Marks Data\n(Internals, Model, University)" --> System
    System -- "Dashboard, Student List,\nMarks Report" --> Staff

    Student -- "Register / Login\nCredentials" --> System
    System -- "Semester Marks,\nSGPA, CGPA Report" --> Student

    System <-- "Read / Write\nAll Records" --> DB
```

---

## Level 1 (Detailed DFD)

Breaks the system into its major processes and shows data stores.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    %% ── External Entities ──
    Staff([🧑‍🏫 Staff])
    Student([🎓 Student])

    %% ── Data Stores ──
    DS1[(D1: User)]
    DS2[(D2: Department)]
    DS3[(D3: Student)]
    DS4[(D4: Mark)]
    DS5[(D5: Semester)]
    DS6[(D6: SubjectTemplate)]

    %% ── Processes ──
    P1["1.0 Authentication\n(Register / Login / Logout)"]
    P2["2.0 Department\nSelection"]
    P3["3.0 Student\nManagement"]
    P4["4.0 Marks\nManagement"]
    P5["5.0 Result\nViewing"]

    %% ── Staff flows ──
    Staff -- "Staff credentials" --> P1
    Staff -- "Select department" --> P2
    Staff -- "Add / Edit / Delete\nstudent details" --> P3
    Staff -- "Enter / Edit / Delete\nmarks data" --> P4

    %% ── Student flows ──
    Student -- "Student credentials" --> P1
    Student -- "Select department" --> P2
    Student -- "View results" --> P5

    %% ── Process 1: Authentication ──
    P1 -- "Create / Verify user" --> DS1
    DS1 -- "User record" --> P1
    P1 -- "Auth status" --> Staff
    P1 -- "Auth status" --> Student

    %% ── Process 2: Department Selection ──
    DS2 -- "Department list" --> P2
    P2 -- "Selected dept stored\nin session" --> P3
    P2 -- "Selected dept stored\nin session" --> P4
    P2 -- "Selected dept stored\nin session" --> P5

    %% ── Process 3: Student Management ──
    P3 -- "Create / Update / Delete" --> DS1
    P3 -- "Create / Update / Delete" --> DS3
    DS3 -- "Student list" --> P3
    P3 -- "Student list &\nconfirmation" --> Staff

    %% ── Process 4: Marks Management ──
    DS5 -- "Semester info" --> P4
    DS6 -- "Subject suggestions" --> P4
    P4 -- "Save / Update / Delete\nmarks" --> DS4
    DS4 -- "Existing marks" --> P4
    P4 -- "Marks table &\nSGPA" --> Staff

    %% ── Process 5: Result Viewing ──
    DS4 -- "All marks\nfor student" --> P5
    DS5 -- "Semester info" --> P5
    P5 -- "Semester marks,\nSGPA, CGPA" --> Student
```

---

## Process Descriptions

| Process | Description | Input | Output | Data Stores Used |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **1.0 Authentication** | Handles staff registration, student registration, login, and logout | Credentials (username, password, role) | Auth status, session token | D1: User, D3: Student |
| **2.0 Department Selection** | Lets users pick a department; stores choice in session | Department ID | Session context | D2: Department |
| **3.0 Student Management** | Staff can add, edit, or delete student records | Student details (name, roll no, phone, year) | Updated student list, confirmations | D1: User, D3: Student |
| **4.0 Marks Management** | Staff enters/edits/deletes marks per student per semester | Mark values (internals, model, university exam) | Marks table, SGPA | D4: Mark, D5: Semester, D6: SubjectTemplate |
| **5.0 Result Viewing** | Students view their marks across all semesters with SGPA & CGPA | Student ID (from session) | Semester-wise marks, SGPA, CGPA | D4: Mark, D5: Semester |

